HEADWORD: Wildness
<hw>Wild"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of being
wild; an uncultivated or untamed state; disposition to rove or go
unrestrained; rudeness; savageness; irregularity; distraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

